<li id="cite_note-Economics_Competition-6"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Economics_Competition_6-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Economics_Competition_6-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Economics_Competition_6-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">Competition from other firms who offer other financial assets that promise the market <a href="/wiki/Rate_of_return" title="Rate of return">rate of return</a> forces the person who is asking for a delay in payment to offer a "discount yield" that is the same as the market rate of return.</span>
